13/Nov/23 3:14 PM;635771987d4645af4f01bd17;Note added by FMC Team in Freshservice:
 
Amadeus update :-


first of all, regarding the error highlighted,
.R/EPAY KK1  CC/XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-5137
-> the format is not correct, character -  should not split the CC, the
ADL should be injected with an EPAY with this format: .R/EPAY KK1
CC/XXXXXXXXXXXX5137




On the 10th of November, the issue regarding the remark elements for
EPAY occured for multiple passengers, which explains why several
bookings are missing.
 
Also, more recently, a few errors like '
Can not Add PAX 1SHEIKH/MOHMEDHANIFADAMMOHMEDMR<0> to PNR. It is not a
group PNR.' have been returned.
The reason is that a booking already exist for that passenger on 1A side
(here, recloc J4W2FF), created by a previous PNL or ADL.
 
If the airline want to UPDATE the information for an existing passenger,
ADL CHG should be used, but not ADL ADD

Dear Team,
 
We are regularly facing the issue that some passengers' confirmation tickets are in Accel
 Aero, but their names are not reflecting in the Altea DCS system. We need to accept them as NREC, which results in a delay in counter closing and also causes passengers to suffer at the counter, which is not good for customer service and shows a bad impression.
On today's flight G9855, we accepted 10 passengers as NOREC. And most of the time, on different
 flights, we observe that one of the group tickets is not updated in the Altea DCS system.
Kindly look into the matter and resolve it permanently in future. Some tickets are attached for your reference.
 



 
Regards,

column577:
17/Jan/24 1:33 PM;635771987d4645af4f01bd17;Note added by Neha Sultana in Freshservice:
 
Dear Requestor  ,

In this case the issue is , when the group booking is split and cancelled at the same time , we first send the DEL for split PNR which has no existence in the DCS side so the ADL will fail to process, 

Ideally  the Group PNR is sent in PNL (PNR - 36296731  group code -A9), when there is split then in ADL the same group code ( A9 ) should first go as DEL instead of A7 and the ADD PNR (group code A7) should be sent .


If the ADL is sent for the ADD of split PNR first and then the DEL for split PNR is sent  its fair scenario, but if the PNR is split and CNX at the same time and ADL is triggered ,

DEL for split PNR is sent without the ADD of split PNR  this is incorrect .

We will raise this issue with our development team and update you once it is fixed.

Regards,
Neha
